Here you can specify the general type of biome the latitudinal
zone as well as the water availability in the biome the data
comes from. For example south China Jianxi region plots would
mean terrestrial, subtropic and semi humid.
Here you can specify the physiognomy of the biome the data
comes. It is specified in two levels.First pick the general
class then select a more specific type. For example an mixed
forest would be forest -> mixed forest. The type list changes
based upon your class selection. Add to list with plus.
Here you can specify the use of the land the data comes from.
For example a study plot in timberland would mean semi-
natural agroforestry. Add a selection with plus button.
